---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="CV">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-6 print:px-0 print:py-0">
    <div class="flex justify-end mb-4 print:hidden">
      <button
        id="copy-cv-btn"
        class="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
        aria-label="Copy CV to clipboard"
      >
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="14" height="14" x="8" y="8" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M4 16c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V4c0-1.1.9-2 2-2h10c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2"/></svg>
        <span>Copy</span>
      </button>
    </div>
    <div id="cv-content">
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1">Education</h2>
        <div class="mb-5">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">University of Exeter</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Exeter, England</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap mb-1">
            <span class="italic">BSc (Hons) Computer Science - predicted high 2:1.</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Sept 2023 — May 2026</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li><strong>Relevant Modules:</strong> Security Assessment and Validation, Software Development, Database Theory and Design, Enterprise Computing, High Performance Computing, Data Science at Scale.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-5">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-start flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Sixth Form</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Wales</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap mb-1">
            <span class="italic">A-Levels: A*A*A (Maths, Physics, CS); AS-Level: A (Chemistry)</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Sept 2016 — June 2023</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1">Awards and Achievements</h2>
        <article class="mb-4">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Hack South West Hackathon 2026 - 2nd place</h3>
            <a href="https://github.com/apex-hinde/HSW-garbo" class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 hover:underline">github.com/apex-hinde/HSW-garbo</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-1">
            <li>As a 4-person team, developed a business logic platform in <strong>Go</strong>, integrating custom <strong>AI</strong> agent skills with <strong>SQLite</strong> to automate payroll and employee management.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="mb-4">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Hack South West CTF 2025 - 2nd place</h3>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-1">
            <li>In a 4-person team, tackled challenges in Network Forensics, <strong>Linux</strong> exploitation, and <strong>Python/Bash</strong> scripting in a competitive environment.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1">Projects</h2>

        <article class="mb-4">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Home Server (Kubernetes + GitOps)</h3>
            <a href="https://github.com/pixel-87/nixos-config" class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 hover:underline">github.com/pixel-87/nixos-config</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-1">
            <li>Architected and operated a 2-node homelab platform using <strong>Linux (NixOS)</strong> and <strong>Kubernetes (K3s)</strong>, with <strong>MetalLB load balancing</strong>, applying <strong>DevOps</strong> practices around automation and observability.</li>
            <li>Implemented a <strong>GitOps</strong>-driven <strong>CI/CD</strong> workflow with <strong>Flux</strong> to automate website deployments.</li>
            <li>Deployed and managed self-hosted services (media, DNS, web hosting, game servers, and automations) for 5+ users.</li>
            <li>Used <strong>Prometheus/Grafana</strong> with <strong>Flux Helm Releases</strong>, plus <strong>alerting</strong> and <strong>metrics dashboards</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="mb-4">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Streak Buttons</h3>
            <a href="https://github.com/pixel-87/duo-streak-widget" class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 hover:underline">github.com/pixel-87/duo-streak-widget</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-1">
            <li>Built a <strong>Go microservice</strong> to generate personal streak buttons/widgets, e.g. Duolingo and GitHub.</li>
            <li>Managed a cloud-native stack with <strong>Infrastructure as Code (Terraform)</strong> on serverless <strong>Google Cloud Platform (GCP)</strong> Cloud Run, behind a <strong>Cloudflare Content Delivery Network (CDN)</strong>.</li>
            <li>Used <strong>GitHub Actions CI</strong> to build <strong>Docker container</strong> images.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="mb-4">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap">
            <h3 class="font-semibold">Personal Website</h3>
            <a href="https://ed-thomas.dev" class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 hover:underline">ed-thomas.dev</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5 mt-1">
            <li>Built a full <strong>CI/CD pipeline</strong> to deploy a <strong>container</strong> on push to my cluster.</li>
            <li>Wrote blog posts on various tech, to document my learning and share my journey.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1">Experience</h2>

        <article class="mb-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Open Source Contributor - nixpkgs</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 whitespace-nowrap">Jan 2026 — Present</span>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li>Reviewed <strong>community pull requests</strong> to ensure code quality.</li>
            <li>Managed the lifecycle of the <strong>TORCS package</strong>, including version bumps, security patching, and build validation.</li>
            <li>Collaborated on a refactor to decouple the binary from 500MB of static assets; avoided <strong>CI cache bloat</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="mb-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Excode Workshop Leader</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 whitespace-nowrap">Sept 2025 — Nov 2025</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">
            Google Developer Student Club (GDSC) — <a href="https://excode.co.uk" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">excode.co.uk</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li>Guided <strong>30+</strong> students through exercises in fundamental <strong>Python</strong> concepts, programme design, and debugging.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="mb-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Social Secretary</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 whitespace-nowrap">Sept 2024 — June 2025</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">
            University of Exeter Climbing Club
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li>Organised weekly socials for <strong>100+</strong> people, coordinating with venues to schedule events and manage logistics.</li>
            <li><strong>Taught</strong> new members climbing fundamentals and safety.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="mb-6">
          <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline flex-wrap mb-1">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Onboarding Assistant</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 whitespace-nowrap">June 2024 — Sept 2024</span>
          </div>
          <div class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">
            Pembrokeshire County Council
          </div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li>Streamlined the daily workflow with <strong>Python</strong> automation for data filtering, <strong>reducing manual processing time</strong> by <strong>60%</strong>.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1">Certificates</h2>
        <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li><strong>GitHub Foundations</strong>, GitHub</li>
          </ul>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Oct 2025</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 pb-1">Skills</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1">
          <li><span class="font-medium">Platform Engineering:</span> Linux (NixOS), Kubernetes (K3s), Docker, GitOps (Flux), Infrastructure as Code (IaC - Terraform), Helm, Prometheus, Grafana, Nixpkgs Maintainer.</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">Programming Languages:</span> Python, Java, Go, SQL, Nix.</li>
          <li><span class="font-medium">Technologies:</span> Git, Django, go-chi, Astro, Google Cloud Platform (GCP).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script>
    const copyBtn = document.getElementById("copy-cv-btn");
    const cvContent = document.getElementById("cv-content");

    copyBtn?.addEventListener("click", async () => {
      if (!cvContent) return;

      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(cvContent.innerText);
        const originalHtml = copyBtn.innerHTML;
        copyBtn.innerHTML = `
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"/></svg>
          <span>Copied!</span>
        `;
        copyBtn.classList.add("text-green-700", "dark:text-green-400", "border-green-300", "dark:border-green-800", "bg-green-50", "dark:bg-green-900/30");
        copyBtn.classList.remove("bg-gray-100", "dark:bg-gray-800", "border-gray-200", "dark:border-gray-700", "text-gray-700", "dark:text-gray-300");

        setTimeout(() => {
          copyBtn.innerHTML = originalHtml;
          copyBtn.classList.remove("text-green-700", "dark:text-green-400", "border-green-300", "dark:border-green-800", "bg-green-50", "dark:bg-green-900/30");
          copyBtn.classList.add("bg-gray-100", "dark:bg-gray-800", "border-gray-200", "dark:border-gray-700", "text-gray-700", "dark:text-gray-300");
        }, 2000);
      } catch (err) {
        console.error("Failed to copy:", err);
      }
    });
  </script>
</Layout>
